  "market_context": "Daily chart showed a bearish break below a key multi-timeframe support/resistance level. 4H confirmed smooth downtrend; price formed a supply zone (order block + FVG) around 161800–162400. 1H initially remained bullish until a CHoCH occurred, aligning LTF with HTF bearish bias.",
  "key_observation": "Price broke below a critical horizontal level that had acted as both support and resistance multiple times, triggering expectation of further downside toward the next structural level.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identified a key horizontal level on the daily chart that had repeatedly served as support and resistance; noted price broke below it.",
    "Step 2: Zoomed into the 4H chart to confirm higher-timeframe bearish trend and identified a supply area (order block + wick extension) between ~161800–162400, marking it as the trading zone.",
    "Step 3: Moved to the 1H chart to refine the 4H order block, but paused entry because 1H structure was still bullish despite HTF bearishness.",
    "Step 4: Waited for and observed a change of character (CHoCH) on the 1H chart, confirming reversal and aligning lower timeframe with HTF direction.",
    "Step 5: After CHoCH confirmation, used the refined 1H order block (pink 161800–162400 and cyan 161000–161800 zones) as the short entry zone."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
  "lessons": "Never trade against the HTF bias; wait for LTF structure to confirm alignment via CHoCH or BOS. Refine HTF order blocks on LTF for precise entries, but only after market structure confirms directional agreement.",
